Maltese: In-negozjati għal ftehim kummerċjali ma' New Zealand bdew f'Ġunju 2018 u ġew konklużi fit-30 ta' Ġunju 2022, meta l-ftehim tħabbar mill-President von der Leyen u mbagħad mill-Prim Ministru ta' New Zealand Ardern.
English: Negotiations for a trade agreement with New Zealand started in June 2018 and were concluded on 30 June 2022, when the deal was announced by President von der Leyen and then New Zealand Prime Minister Ardern.

English: Sections 2.2 and 2.3 on liquidity support in form of State guarantees and subsidised loans, and section 2.7 on measures aimed at supporting electricity demand reduction have already phased-out on 31 December 2023; while

Maltese: L-UE talloka EUR 4.5 miljun għal 324 proġett tax-xjenzati Ukreni biex ikomplu r-riċerka tagħhom
English: EU allocates €4.5 million for 324 Ukrainian scientists' projects to pursue their research

Maltese: F'April 2023, il-proġett Eurizon iffinanzjat mill-UE nieda l-Programm ta' Boroż ta' Studju “Għotjiet ta' Riċerka Remota għar-Riċerkaturi mill-Ukrajna”.
English: In April 2023, the EU-funded EURIZON project launched their Fellowship Programme ‘Remote Research Grants for Researchers from Ukraine'.

Maltese: Jistgħu jiskopru wkoll l-inizjattivi ffinanzjati mill-BEI bħall-isptarijiet lokali, l-infrastruttura tat-trasport bħall-ferroviji jew il-metros, jew bħall-ilqugħ għall-għargħar li jissalvagwardja l-irħula tagħhom.
English: They may also discover EIB-funded initiatives such as local hospitals, transportation infrastructure like trains or metros, or flood barriers safeguarding their hometowns.

Maltese: Meta jżuru l-bini tal-KESE, il-viżitaturi se jkunu jistgħu wkoll jilqgħu lill-membri u l-persunal tal-KESE hekk kif itemmu tellieqa bir-roti biex iqajmu kuxjenza dwar l-elezzjonijiet Ewropej.
English: When visiting the EESC building, visitors will also be able to welcome EESC members and staff as they finish a cycling race to raise awareness on the European elections.

Maltese: Se jkunu jistgħu jinteraġixxu huma u jisimgħu informazzjoni relatata mal-UE u jipparteċipaw fi kwiżż b'ċans li jirbħu premju!
English: They will be able to engage with EU-related information and participate in a quiz for a chance to win a prize!

Maltese: Fl-20 ta' Novembru 2023, il-Kummissjoni adottat estensjoni limitata għal ċerti tipi ta' għajnuna fid-dawl tad-distorsjonijiet persistenti tas-suq, b'mod partikolari fis-settur tal-enerġija.
English: On 20 November 2023, the Commission adopted a limited prolongation for certain types of aid in view of the persisting market distortions, particularly in the energy sector.

Maltese: Ir-regoli agrikoli de minimis ġew riveduti l-aħħar fl-2019 u se jkunu jeħtieġu reviżjoni qabel il-31 ta' Diċembru 2027, id-data li bħalissa fiha għandhom jiskadu.
English: The Agricultural de minimis rules were last revised in 2019 and will need a revision before they are currently set to expire on 31 December 2027.

Maltese: Iċ-ċittadini se jkunu mistiedna jipparteċipaw f'dibattiti, spettakli live, logħob u attivitajiet oħra.
English: Citizens will be invited to participate in debates, live performances, games and other activities.

Maltese: B'kollox, 65 proġett, inklużi 324 xjenzat Ukren se jibbenefikaw mill-Programm ta' Boroż ta' Studju.
English: In total, 65 projects, including 324 Ukrainian scientists will benefit from the Fellowship Programme.

Maltese: L-invażjoni tal-Ukrajna mir-Russja ġabet magħha sfidi ta' kuljum għar-riċerkaturi.
English: Russia's invasion of Ukraine has brought daily challenges to researchers.

Maltese: 38 % xjenza Fiżika u Inġinerija
English: 38% Physical Science and Engineering

Maltese: L-aġenda sħiħa tinsab hawnhekk.
English: Full agenda here.

Maltese: Dan se jagħti lill-Istati Membri aktar żmien biex jimplimentaw miżuri ta' appoġġ, jekk ikun meħtieġ.
English: It will give Member States more time to implement support measures, if needed.

Maltese: Għalhekk, l-Istati Membri se jkomplu jkunu jistgħu jipprovdu lill-kumpaniji affettwati mill-kriżi jew mis-sanzjonijiet u l-kontrosanzjonijiet sussegwenti, inkluż mir-Russja, sa EUR 280,000 għas-settur agrikolu u sa EUR 335,000 għas-setturi tas-sajd u tal-akkwakultura.
English: Member States will therefore continue to be able to provide companies affected by the crisis or by the subsequent sanctions and countersanctions, including by Russia, up to €280,000 for the agricultural sector and up to €335,000 for the fisheries and aquaculture sectors.

Maltese: Il-Qorti Ewropea tal-Awdituri
English: European Court of Auditors

Maltese: Fid-9 ta' Mejju, l-awdituri tal-UE fil-Lussemburgu se joffru logħob interattiv u affaxxinanti, u l-possibbiltà li ċ-ċittadini jipparteċipaw fi kwiżż biex jittestjaw il-ħiliet tal-awditjar tagħhom.
English: On 9 May, EU auditors in Luxembourg will offer interactive engaging games, and a possibility for citizens to take a quiz to test their audit skills.

Maltese: New Zealand lestiet il-proċedura ta' ratifika tagħha fil-25 ta' Marzu 2024.
English: New Zealand completed its ratification procedure on 25 March 2024.

English: Non-discriminatory treatment of EU investors in New Zealand.

English: European Parliament

Maltese: F'dan l-isfond, il-Kummissjoni ddeċidiet li tadotta estensjoni limitata tat-taqsima 2.1 tat-TCTF għas-settur agrikolu primarju, kif ukoll għas-setturi tas-sajd u tal-akkwakultura.
English: Against this background, the Commission has decided to adopt a limited prolongation of section 2.1 of the TCTF for the primary agricultural sector, as well as the fisheries and aquaculture sectors.

Maltese: Il-Bank Ewropew tal-Investiment
English: European Investment Bank

Maltese: It-Taqsima 2.4, li tippermetti lill-Istati Membri jagħtu għajnuna biex tikkumpensa għall-prezzijiet għoljin tal-enerġija, se tiġi eliminata gradwalment ukoll sat-30 ta' Ġunju 2024;
English: Section 2.4, allowing Member States to grant aid to compensate for high energy prices, will also phase out by 30 June 2024;

Maltese: Xi wħud diġà bdew l-attività tagħhom, bl-aħħar grupp ta' proġetti jirċievi l-għotjiet tagħhom u jibda mill-1 ta' Mejju.
English: Some have already begun their activity, with the last group of projects receiving their grants and starting as of 1 May.

Maltese: L-investiment tal-UE fi New Zealand għandu l-potenzjal li jikber b'massimu ta' 80 %.
English: EU investment into New Zealand has the potential to grow by up to 80%.

English: More information here.

Maltese: Biex tipprovdi appoġġ kontinwu għar-riċerka Ukrena, il-Kummissjoni ttriplikat il-baġit inizjali tal-Programm ta' Boroż ta' Studju Eurizon għal EUR 4.5 miljun taħt Orizzont Ewropa.
English: To provide continuous support to Ukrainian research, the Commission has tripled the initial budget of the EURIZON Fellowship Programme to €4.5 million under Horizon Europe.
